channel.title: Big problem! Real!
channel.description: Look, i can't put me server online! I don't got wireless internet, just cable. After i portforwarded, (with the server run on) i try to login with me ip, and it doesn't work! I try to login with no-ip, It doesn't work! Do i need wireless internet? Oh, and if i don't need wireless internet and the problem is resolved, do's me internet go slower if people connect/try to?

item.title: Big problem! Real!
item.dc:creator: @pk3r_john pk3r john
item.description:
@pk3r_john wrote:

You probably screwed up portforwarding. Try doing it with uTorrent. www.utorrent.com << I think it is. Theres a tut on how to do in the tut section.

And your internet might go slower, but you won’t even notice it. (Unless you have 500+ people on your server)
